Label: dct:created
Definition: For expressing when the documentation (e.g. DPIA Necessity Assessment, or DPIA Procedure, or DPIA outcome) was created

Label: dct:modified
Definition: For expressing when the documentation (e.g. DPIA Necessity Assessment, or DPIA Procedure, or DPIA outcome) was last modified

Label: dct:dateSubmitted
Definition: For expressing when the documentation (e.g. DPIA Necessity Assessment, or DPIA Procedure, or DPIA outcome) was submitted for audit or approval

Label: dct:dateAccepted
Definition: For expressing when the documentation (e.g. DPIA Necessity Assessment, or DPIA Procedure, or DPIA outcome) was accepted through audit or approval

Label: dct:temporal
Definition: For expressing the temporal coverage of the DPIA document or process

Label: dct:valid
Definition: For expressing the temporal date or range of validity of the DPIA document or process. This refers to the time period for which the DPIA is considered valid, and does not refer to the temporal period associated with processing (see dct:temporal instead). The assumption is that after this period, the DPIA should be re-evaluated or some process should be triggered

Label: dct:conformsTo
Definition: For expressing an existing standard, guideline, or requirements to which the DPIA document or process will be conforming to. This could be external guidelines published by an Authority, or internal guidelines established by the organisation

Label: dct:title
Definition: Indicates a title of the DPIA for human comprehension

Label: dct:description
Definition: Indicates a description of the DPIA for human comprehension

Label: dct:identifier
Definition: Indicates an identifier associated with the DPIA documentation or process. Identifiers may be reused from existing systems, or created for the purposes of record management

Label: dct:isVersionOf
Definition: For expressing prior versions or iterations of the DPIA document or process

Label: dct:subject
Definition: For expressing the subject of the DPIA document or process, where subject refers to the point of focus. For expressing what is affected or included within the DPIA, please see dct:coverage

Label: dct:coverage
Definition: For expressing coverage (e.g. jurisdictions, products, services) of the DPIA document or process. For temporal coverage, please see dct:temporal. The coverage can be expressed using dpv:PersonalDataHandling, or using another concept, or even be a link or reference to a document, or a textual description

Label: dpv:hasStatus
Definition: For expressing the status of the DPIA document or process. Here different statuses are used to convey different contextual meanings. For example, dpv:ActivityStatus expresses the state of the activity in terms of whether it is ongoing or completed, and dpv:AuditStatus expresses the state of the audit process in terms of being required, approved, or rejected. These are applied over each step of the DPIA i.e. DPIANecessityAssessment, DPIAProcedure, and DPIAOutcome. Similarly, a process also uses hasStatus with DPIAConformity to indicate adherence to the results of the DPIA process.

Label: dct:hasPart
Definition: For expressing something contains a DPIA document or process contains as a part. For example, as some dpv:DPIA dct:hasPart DPIANecessityAssessment

Label: dct:isPartOf
Definition: For expressing a DPIA document or process is part of another. For example, as some DPIANecessityAssessment dct:isPartOf some dpv:DPIA
